08/05/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Interior Minister Ivica Dacic announced on Friday (May 6th) that Brazilian police have arrested at least four Serbian citizens as part of a crackdown on an international cocaine smuggling ring. According to Dacic, Goran Nesic, who has been sentenced to eight years in prison in Serbia for drug smuggling is also among the arrested. The minister said the operation, in which a total of 17 people were detained, was carried out in a join effort between Brazilian and Serbian police and the US Anti-Drug Agency (DEA). The Brazilian police said that eight of the arrested are Serbians, and that authorities in Belgrade have requested the extradition of the man suspected to be the gang's leader. (Emportal, B92, Beta - 06/05/11)
